<p>United States Consulate
at St Paul de Loanda S.W.C.A.</p>

<p>L de R. du Verge
to State Depart.</p>

<p>Subjects
Temporally leave of absence</p>

<p>Encloses
Request and causes for the same</p>

<pb facs="teaa.en.letter.0161.002"/>
<note>18</note>

<p>United States Consulate
St Paul de Loanda
October 15th 1882</p>

<p>Hon. J.C. Bancroft Davis
Asst. Sectry. of State
Washington D.C.</p>
<p>How: John Davis
Att. Secty. of State
Washington D. C.</p>

<p>Sir
In consideration of the unhealthy state of 
this locality at times, I would most respectfully
solicit the Depart of State, for a standing
permissions to leave this consulate in charge
of the Vice, or actg. vice consul, whenever
circumstances and urgency in case of
sickness may compel me to leave Loanda
for a few weeks further North or South as
may be directed by the Doctors</p>

<p>This request may appear to you from
one who has but just joined his past
of duty, to be a departure from diligent
principles of the Depart. but I trust
that the special nature of my humble
request many induce you and the Hon:
Sectry of State to be the matter into
favorable consideration.</p>

<p>Having consular agencies further North 
and South I may be able if such 
is granted to me, to see personally

<pb facs="teaa.en.letter.0161.003"/>
how the agencies are and instruct them
in their duties toward the U.S. govt.
commerce, shipping <unclear/></p>

<p>I have been sick for over a month with 
Bilious or green fever and have tried to
perform the duties I have been intrusted 
with the best of my ability</p>

<p>I have the honor to be 
Sir
Your obedient servant
L de R. du Verge
US. Consul </p>

